# Let's Code: Python Exercises | Jun2022

> Objective:
> In this challenges I am training basic python skills in 9 exercises.

> Idex:
>
> > ex01 - Write a program that asks the user for a number and prints all numbers from one to the number the user enters.
while | for

> > ex02 - Create a program that reads any value and displays a message telling which range this value is in.
comparison operators | if | elif

> > ex03 - Create a function that takes the value of the radius of a circle as a parameter and returns the value of the area of that circle.
math library

> > ex04 - Write a program that asks for 2 integers and a real number, calculates and displays.
arithmetic operators | int | float

> > ex05 - Let's make a program to control who is the murderer of a crime.
comparison operators | if | elif

> > ex06 - Write a function that takes a list of numbers and returns the sum of the elements in that list.
array | while | for

> > ex07 - Write a program that reads the coordinates of 2 (two) points on a 2D Cartesian plane. Then calculate the Euclidean distance between the points..
math library | array | float

> > ex08 - Calculate the sum of a thousand terms of the inverses of the factorials.
while

> > ex09 - Create (manually or by drawing numbers) a list of 10 numbers and print...
random library | for | manipulating array

